        <prompt>What was General John Pershing's main contribution to WWI?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">He negotiated the peace treaty</option>
            <option letter="b">He commanded American forces in Europe</option>
            <option letter="c">He developed new weapons</option>
            <option letter="d">He organized war funding</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>General John Pershing commanded the American Expeditionary Forces in Europe during WWI, insisting on keeping US forces independent and leading them in major battles like the Meuse-Argonne Offensive.</explanation>
